[div class=p 
	"Major/minor indicates a 16-bit value. The "major" value is multiplied by 256 (240 in the case of the Y-coordinate) and the "minor" value is added to that.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Tricks 
	"Tricks
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"(paraphrased from the TAS submission)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Movement
	]b
	": Gizmo always moves at 1.5 pixels per frame, no matter what direction. This means zig-zagging is just as fast as walking straight.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"Stage finish boost
	]b
	": After finishing a stage, you can walk around while the music is still playing. The way Gizmo is facing when the music stops will give a 1 frame boost in that direction in the next stage.
	$LF
]div
